    <a href="mailto:chrisjoy@sent.com">chrisjoy@sent.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Working Life</h2>

  <p>
    I worked as a software and support developer in the private sector, initially at a then-<a href="https://www.novachem.com">Fortune 500 company</a>,
    where I developed and maintained software for the chemical industry, provided technical support to clients,
    trained users, and built documentation repositories. I then moved into roles at smaller and mid-sized
    companies, eventually starting my own company with a former colleague. After selling the company,
    I spent several years consulting for small and mid-sized businesses in the US and Southeast Asia
    prior to the COVID-19 pandemic. Following that, I returned to graduate school to pursue my
    interests in economics and Southeast Asia.
  </p>

  <h2>Education</h2>

  <p>
    I hold an MSc in Development Economics and an MA in Southeast Asian Studies from
    <a href="http://www.city.ac.uk">City, University of London</a> and
    <a href="https://www.soas.ac.uk/">SOAS, University of London</a> respectively.
    I did my undergraduate work at the <a href="http://www.pitt.edu">University of Pittsburgh</a>
    in Finance and Computer Science.
  </p>

  <h2>Currently</h2>

  <p>
    Reading <em>Seeing Like a State</em> by James C. Scott.
    Writing a project on Viet Nam and US tariffs.
  </p>
